<p style="text-align:left">BaneCare Management has been a trusted family name in senior care services for over 50 years, providing high quality skilled nursing and rehabilitation throughout Massachusetts.<br /> <br /> In 1959, George Bane, BaneCare founder and entrepreneur, sold his successful housewares and clothing business and purchased his first skilled nursing center in Lynn, Massachusetts.<br /> <br /> Now under the direction of George&rsquo;s son, Richard Bane, the company has grown into one of Massachusetts premier long-term care organizations, managing seven skilled nursing and rehabilitation facilities in the greater Boston area and own and operate five skilled nursing and rehabilitation facilities on the South Shore. Skilled nursing centers are located in: Braintree, Brighton, Dalton, Dorchester, Duxbury, Hingham, Hyde Park, Marblehead, Peabody, Pittsfield, Quincy, Swampscott and Weymouth.<br /> <br /> BaneCare nursing centers are a &ldquo;bridge&rdquo; between the hospital and home whether an individual needs a short stay before returning home or requires ongoing care when challenges are too great at home.<br /> <br /> Founder George Bane&rsquo;s mantra, &ldquo;a matter of trust,&rdquo; has formed the foundation for BaneCare today &ndash; joining traditional family values with advanced medical skills and technologies.<br /> <br /> BaneCare, which includes third generation Bane family members, expanded beyond its original community roots to become a highly valued partner of multiple health systems across Massachusetts. With the evolution of the Accountable Care Organization (ACO), BaneCare skilled nursing facilities are considered the provider of choice for many emerging ACOs, including Partners Health Care, Steward Health Care and Lahey Health. BaneCare staff maintain a commitment to the highest level of care, which is reflected in BaneCare&rsquo;s national rankings*, certifications and awards. &nbsp;<br /> <br /> <em>*BaneCare facilities are consistently rated higher than national averages based on approved national quality measures for skilled nursing and long-term healthcare facilities. <a href="https://www.medicare.gov/nursinghomecompare/search.html" target="_blank">Click here for more information.</a></em></p>  <p style="text-align:left">&nbsp;</p>  <hr /> <div style="background:#eee;border:1px solid #ccc;padding:5px 35px;"> <p>&nbsp;</p>  <p><strong><img alt="BaneCare - Richard Bane, President" class="shadow" src="/apps/_ee/files/richard-bane.jpg" style="float:left; height:209px; margin-bottom:10px; margin-right:20px; width:225px" /><span style="font-size:18px"><span style="color:rgb(4, 82, 134)">Richard Bane, President</span></span></strong></p>  <p style="margin-left:.5in"><em>&ldquo;The world of long-term care is changing very quickly,&rdquo; says Richard Bane, president of BaneCare Management. &ldquo;We are not what people typically associate with a &lsquo;nursing home&rsquo;. Our facilities are technologically advanced and our staff is trained to handle complex medical situations. Our clinical expertise comes with a personal touch, because we truly care.&rdquo; </em></p>  <p>President Richard Bane and BaneCare continue to set the standard for premium skilled nursing care in Massachusetts.</p>  <p>A leading authority in the region&rsquo;s long-term care field, Bane lectures across the country and acts as chair of The Aurum Network, the largest post-acute network of independent skilled care providers in New England. A recent past chair of the Massachusetts Senior Care Association, Richard is a key decision maker for the entire Massachusetts skilled care community, leading efforts in Accountable Care.<br /> &nbsp;</p> </div> 